acter is part of a contiguous sequence representing the ten\ndecimal digits in order from 0 to 9, this function returns the first and\nlast characters from this range.\n\nUnicode property: `Numeric_Type=Decimal` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L709-L712","name":"Unicode.isDecimal","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isDecimal","doc":"Check if character represents a decimal digit\n\nFor this property, a character must be part of a contiguous sequence\nrepresenting the ten decimal digits in order from 0 to 9.\n\nUnicode property: `Numeric_Type=Decimal` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L686-L701","name":"Unicode.getDigit?","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getDigit?","doc":"Get value of digit\n\nUnicode properties: `Numeric_Value`, `Numeric_Type=Digit` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L672-L680","name":"Unicode.isDigit","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isDigit","doc":"Check if character represents a digit in base 10\n\nUnicode property: `Numeric_Type=Digit` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L652-L661","name":"Unicode.getCanonicalDecomposition.loop","kind":"opaque","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getCanonicalDecomposition.loop","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L640-L662","name":"Unicode.getCanonicalDecomposition","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getCanonicalDecomposition","doc":"Get canonical decomposition of character (`NFD`)\n\nUnicode property: `Decomposition_Mapping` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L628-L631","name":"Unicode.getTitleChar","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getTitleChar","doc":"Map character to titlecase\n\nThis function does not handle the case where the titlecase mapping would\nconsist of more than one character.\n\nUnicode property: `Simple_Titlecase_Mapping` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L616-L619","name":"Unicode.getUpperChar","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getUpperChar","doc":"Map character to uppercase\n\nThis function does not handle the case where the uppercase mapping would\nconsist of more than one character.\n\nUnicode property: `Simple_Uppercase_Mapping` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L604-L607","name":"Unicode.getLowerChar","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getLowerChar","doc":"Map character to lowercase\n\nThis function does not handle the case where the lowercase mapping would\nconsist of more than one character.\n\nUnicode property: `Simple_Lowercase_Mapping` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L589-L589","name":"Unicode.GeneralCategory.isCn","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.GeneralCategory.isCn","doc":"Check if unassigned character (`Cn`)\n\nUnicode Property: `General_Category=Cn` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L583-L586","name":"Unicode.GeneralCategory.isUnassigned","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.GeneralCategory.isUnassigned","doc":"Check if unassigned character (`Cn`)\n\nUnicode Property: `General_Category=Cn` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/l