LowercaseLetter","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.GeneralCategory.isLowercaseLetter","doc":"Check if lowercase letter character (`Ll`)\n\nUnicode Property: `General_Category=Ll` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L130-L130","name":"Unicode.GeneralCategory.isL","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.GeneralCategory.isL","doc":"Check if letter character (`L`)\n\nThis is a derived category (`L = Lu | Ll | Lt | Lm | Lo`).\n\nUnicode Property: `General_Category=L` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L124-L127","name":"Unicode.GeneralCategory.isLetter","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.GeneralCategory.isLetter","doc":"Check if letter character (`L`)\n\nThis is a derived category (`L = Lu | Ll | Lt | Lm | Lo`).\n\nUnicode Property: `General_Category=L` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L107-L114","name":"Unicode.isInGeneralCategory","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isInGeneralCategory","doc":"Check if character belongs to the general category\n\nUnicode property: `General_Category` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L101-L102","name":"Unicode.getGeneralCategory","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getGeneralCategory","doc":"Get character general category\n\n*Caveat*: This function never returns a derived general category. Use\n`Unicode.isInGeneralCategory` to check whether a character belongs to a\ngeneral category (derived or not).\n\nUnicode property: `General_Category` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L82-L87","name":"Unicode.isBidiControl","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isBidiControl","doc":"Check if bidirectional control character\n\nUnicode property: `Bidi_Control` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L76-L77","name":"Unicode.isBidiMirrored","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isBidiMirrored","doc":"Check if bidirectional mirrored character\n\nUnicode property: `Bidi_Mirrored` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L70-L71","name":"Unicode.getBidiClass","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getBidiClass","doc":"Get character bidirectional class\n\nUnicode property: `Bidi_Class` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/c7360dcdfc4ef13e1accbe83280656d8348839fa/UnicodeBasic.lean#L60-L61","name":"Unicode.getName","kind":"def","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getName","doc":"Get character name\n\nWhen the Unicode property `Name` is empty, a unique code label is returned\nas described in Unicode Standard, section 4.8. These labels start with\n`'<'` (U+003C) and end with `'>'` (U+003E) so they are distinguishable from\nactual name values.\n\nUnicode property: `Name`\n"}]}